# gen109 (L17, prose) — the bilingual ratchet (LOOP.md). The operation is chosen
# from semantic cues, so Italian verbs (compra/mangia/ciascuna) map to the same
# operators through the same code path — no English sentence templates. Numbers
# are language-neutral; only the cue words differ. Same solver.

# "compra" (buys) -> addition.
> Marco ha 8 mele e ne compra 5. Quante mele ha?
< 13.
# "mangia" + "rimangono" (eats / are left) -> subtraction.
> Anna aveva 10 caramelle e ne mangia 3. Quante ne rimangono?
< 7.
# "ciascuna" (each) -> multiplication.
> Ci sono 6 scatole con 4 palline ciascuna. Quante palline in totale?
< 24.